git commit -m "feat: add filename sanitization and configurable folder cleanup\
\
\
\
- rename files containing spaces by replacing spaces with underscores\
\
- add containsSpaces helper for filename validation\
\
- introduce removeSpacesInFolder to sanitize filenames before processing\
\
- add cleanFolder function to separate sorting logic from main\
\
- support custom target path via CLI argument\
\
- default to ~/Downloads when no path is provided\
\
- improve file move logging with full source and destination paths\
\
- refactor os.Rename calls using explicit old_path/new_path variables\
\
- skip directory entries during cleanup and sanitization\
\
- change empty extension mapping from 'other' to 'noName'\
\
- avoid moving files when no folder mapping exists\
\
- improve program structure by extracting reusable helpers"
git add
git add .
git commit -m "refactor: modularize file organizer with space handling and CLI path support\
\
- Rename empty-extension category from 'other' to 'noName' for clarity\
\
- Extract file-moving logic into cleanFolder() and move main loop out\
  of main(), separating concerns between orchestration and execution\
\
- Add removeSpacesInFolder() and helpers containsSpaces() / removeSpaces()\
  to normalize filenames before sorting, replacing spaces with underscores\
\
- Introduce path variables (old_path / new_path) in moveFileToFolder()\
  for improved readability and accurate move confirmation logs\
\
- Fix move confirmation message to print full source/destination paths\
  instead of just the filename and folder name\
\
- Accept CLI argument for target path (os.Args[1]); fall back to\
  $HOME/Downloads/ when no argument is provided, replacing hardcoded path\
\
- Remove stale comments ('ignore folders', 'error panick', duplicate\
  name-collision comment) and clean up surrounding whitespace\
\
- Skip files with unrecognized extensions (folder == '') instead of\
  attempting to move them to an empty-string destination"
